column5: Red Breasted Merganser, poor bugger. Didn't seem any worse for wear. At least he didn't swallow the hooks.
id submit this for a world record lol Biggest bird caught through ice.
The full run toward the open water had me as surprised as the bird. I, like the bird, am an ice chicken.
Wow, that was cool, glad the bird was ok and did not swallow the hook
Crazy guys fishing that close to open water on a river. IMO.  Very cool video though!
yup, too close to the open lead for my taste, current or not current.
Why did that seem set up to me? Cool vid though!

I'm with Algoma Guy here. Do they run to the hole with camera filming every time they get a hit? If they did it on purpose they should have the same thing done to them, if not, well I don't know what to say I have never heard of a bird ever pulled up a hole. And am glad no animals were harmed. As far as too close to the hole, I got blasted for saying the same thing earlier in this ice season when I said the guy was nuts for doing so.
I'm not a fan of these winter birds.  They chase my lures when I'm casting in the winter.  I had one pick up my bait on the bottom and bring it up to the surface, I was lucky it didn't get hooked.
